#: main_12.cpp:2895
msgid "When I was writing the code for engine matches, I found that the Stockfish"
msgstr ""

#: main_12.cpp:2897
msgid "and Komodo engines were losing on time in games with a fast time limit,"
msgstr ""

#: main_12.cpp:2899
msgid "so I wrote the < Engine time adjustment > option to fix this problem."
msgstr ""

#: main_12.cpp:2902
msgid "With a rated game, using a longer time limit, I found that once again"
msgstr ""

#: main_12.cpp:2904
msgid "Stockfish plays its moves very slowly when it is out of its opening book"
msgstr ""

#: main_12.cpp:2906
msgid "or if no book is used."
msgstr ""

#: main_12.cpp:2909
msgid "To remedy this you can adjust the Stockfish slow mover option."
msgstr ""

#: main_12.cpp:2911
msgid "Lowering this value speeds up the moves a bit."
msgstr ""

#: main_12.cpp:2913
msgid "Although I found this option was not adequate for fast time controls"
msgstr ""

#: main_12.cpp:2915
msgid "of 3 minutes or less for a game, it works well for 5 minutes or greater."
msgstr ""

#: main_12.cpp:2917
msgid "For Stockfish 11, a value of 20-30 works well for 5-10 minute games."
msgstr ""

#: main_12.cpp:2920
msgid "You can set the slow mover option using the custom parameter options"
msgstr ""

#: main_12.cpp:2922
msgid "in the engine dialog box."
msgstr ""

#: main_12.cpp:2924
msgid "To make things easier, I have made an engine parameter file for Stockfish 11"
msgstr ""

#: main_12.cpp:2926
msgid "with the slow mover set.  You can load this from the rated game dialog box"
msgstr ""

#: main_12.cpp:2928
msgid "by clicking on engine < Engine settings.. > and then < Load engine >"
msgstr ""

#: main_12.cpp:2930
msgid "from the engine dialog box that opens."
msgstr ""

#: main_12.cpp:2933
msgid "The parameter files for Stockfish11 are stored in the directory"
msgstr ""

#: main_12.cpp:2938
msgid "Stockfish engines 8-15 have the slow mover option, 16 and 17 do not."
msgstr ""

#: main_12.cpp:2940
msgid "Given the fact that you do not need the extra playing strength here,"
msgstr ""

#: main_12.cpp:2942
msgid "there is no need to use the stronger engines."
msgstr ""

#: main_12.cpp:2960
msgid "I found this version of the Stockfish engine on the GitHub at -"
msgstr ""

#: main_12.cpp:2964
msgid "It is a more adjustable version than the standard engine."
msgstr ""

#: main_12.cpp:2966
msgid "Here is a description of the engine from the < README.md > file -"
msgstr ""

#: main_12.cpp:2971
msgid "StockfishNPS is a slightly modified Stockfish for human play"
msgstr ""

#: main_12.cpp:2973
msgid "with nodes per second reduction, (kilo nodes per second ~= 1 / waitms"
msgstr ""

#: main_12.cpp:2975
msgid "randomized evaluation, search depth and search nodes limit."
msgstr ""

#: main_12.cpp:2977
msgid "The strength of the first two modifications can be set in the uci options"
msgstr ""

#: main_12.cpp:2979
msgid "from 0 to 100, while search depth may be limited to values from 1 to 20"
msgstr ""

#: main_12.cpp:2981
msgid "and search nodes to values up to 500000."
msgstr ""

#: main_12.cpp:2984
msgid "All modifications can be used in any combination together with"
msgstr ""

#: main_12.cpp:2986
msgid "ELO limit strength and Skill Level settings, to reduce the strength"
msgstr ""

#: main_12.cpp:2988
msgid "of the engine when playing against humans."
msgstr ""

#: main_12.cpp:2991
msgid "With default settings, StockfishNPS plays exactly like the current Stockfish16_dev."
msgstr ""

#: main_12.cpp:2993
msgid "Changing only the search nodes setting to between 1 - 10 reduces ELO roughly to 1400."
msgstr ""

#: main_12.cpp:2995
msgid "That's a good starting point for additional option changes."
msgstr ""

#: main_12.cpp:3000
msgid "I think that this means that a higher < waitms > value reduces"
msgstr ""

#: main_12.cpp:3002
msgid "the number of positions that the engine searches per second."
msgstr ""

#: main_12.cpp:3004
msgid "Increasing the randomized evaluation value"
msgstr ""

#: main_12.cpp:3006
msgid "will lead to more varied play."
msgstr ""

#: main_12.cpp:3008
msgid "< Search nodes > imposes some kind of limit on the number of positions searched."
